HEADWORD: Solenodon
<hw>So*le"no*don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/
a channel + <?/<?/<?/<?/, <?/<?/<?/, a tooth.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Either one of two species of singular West Indian insectivores,
allied to the tenrec. One species (<spn>Solendon paradoxus</spn>),
native of St. Domingo, is called also <stype>agouta</stype>; the other
(<spn>Solendon Cubanus</spn>), found in Cuba, is called
<stype>almique</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solenogastra</ent>⟦br⟧
